==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Poco
<hw>Po"co</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[It.]</ety>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A little; -- used chiefly in phrases indicating
the time or movement; <as>as, <ex>poco</ex> pi⟦ugrave⟧ allegro, a little
faster; <ex>poco</ex> largo, rather slow.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>\'d8Poco a poco</b></col> <ety>[It.]</ety>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <cd>Little by little; as, <xex>poco a poco</xex>
crescendo, gradually increasing in loudness.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pocock</ent>⟦br⟧
